{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Bitvector_Enum.Bitvector_Forward</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":true,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"codex","href":"../../../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Single_value_abstraction","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Log","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Sig","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Bitvector_Enum","href":"../index.html","kind":"module-type"},{"name":"Bitvector_Forward","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biadd\"><a href=\"#val-biadd\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biadd : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Flags/Biadd/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Biadd.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector Integer ADDition. Operaters on bitvectors of size <code>size</code>. The flags represent behavior on overflow:</p><ul><li><code>nuw</code>: no unsigned wrap: the operation is partial, i.e. fails if the sum of the two operands (interpreted as unsigned numbers) is not in the <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">0</code> to <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">2^{size}-1</code> interval.</li></ul><ul><li><code>nsw</code>: no signed wrap: the operation is partial, i.e. fails if the sum of the two operands (interpreted as signed numbers) is not in the <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">-2^{size-1}</code> to<code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">2^{size-1} - 1</code> interval.</li></ul><ul><li><code>nusw</code>: no unsigned plus signed wrap: the addition of the first operand (interpreted as an unsigned number) and the second one (interpreted as a signed number) fails if its value is not in the <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">0</code> to <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">2^{size}-1</code> interval. This is useful when doing pointer arithmetic (address (unsigned) + offset (signed))</li></ul><p>Note that the simultaneous combination of different flags may be unimplemented (as it never happens in practice).</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bisub\"><a href=\"#val-bisub\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bisub : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Flags/Biadd/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Biadd.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector Integer SUBtraction. See <a href=\"#val-biadd\"><code>biadd</code></a> for the flag meanings</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bimul\"><a href=\"#val-bimul\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bimul : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Flags/Bimul/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Bimul.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector Integer MULtiplication. See <a href=\"#val-biadd\"><code>biadd</code></a> for the flag meanings</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bshl\"><a href=\"#val-bshl\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bshl : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">flags</span>:<a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Flags/Bshl/index.html#type-t\">Operator.Flags.Bshl.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector SHift Left, If second argument is larger than size, bshl returns 0.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bashr\"><a href=\"#val-bashr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bashr : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Arithmetic shift right: fill with the most significant bit.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-blshr\"><a href=\"#val-blshr\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> blshr : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Logical shift right: fill with 0.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-beq\"><a href=\"#val-beq\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> beq : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector equality</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bisle\"><a href=\"#val-bisle\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bisle : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Signed comparison between two bitvectors (using less-or-equal <code>&lt;=</code>). Bitvectors are interpreted as integers in <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">[-2^{size-1}..-2^{size-1}-1]</code> using two's complement.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-biule\"><a href=\"#val-biule\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> biule : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-boolean\">boolean</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Unsigned comparison between two bitvectors (using less-or-equal <code>&lt;=</code>). Bitvectors are interpreted as positive integers in <code class=\"odoc-katex-math\">[0..-2^{size}-1]</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bconcat\"><a href=\"#val-bconcat\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bconcat : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size1</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size2</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector concatenation: the new bitvector's size is the sum of the sizes of the arguments. The first argument becomes the most significant bits.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bextract\"><a href=\"#val-bextract\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bextract : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">index</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">oldsize</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar1\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar1</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Extract a <code>size</code> of a bitvector of total size <code>oldsize</code>, starting at <code>index</code>. Should satisfy <code>index + size &lt;= oldsize</code>.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-band\"><a href=\"#val-band\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> band : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>, <a href=\"../index.html#type-bitvector\">bitvector</a>)</span> <a href=\"../../../../../Operator/Sig/Forward_Arity/index.html#type-ar2\">Operator.Forward_Arity.ar2</a></span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Bitvector bitwise and</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-bor\"><a href=\"#val-bor\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> bor : \u000A  <span><span class=\"label\">size</span>:int <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span>\u000A  <span><span>(<a href=\"../i